+ Select the Right\nNumeric Type
++ Whole Numbers
+++ TINYINT
++++_ -128 to 127, 1 byte
++++_ Status codes
+++ SMALLINT
++++_ -32k to 32k, 2 bytes
++++_ Year values
+++ INT
++++_ ±2.1 billion, 4 bytes
++++_ IDs and counts
+++ BIGINT
++++_ ±9.2 quintillion, 8 bytes
++++_ Large IDs, row counts
-- Decimal Numbers
--- DECIMAL(p,s)
----_ Exact precision
----_ Financial data
----_ p = total digits, s = after decimal
--- FLOAT / DOUBLE
----_ Approximate
----_ Scientific calculations
----_ Rounding errors possible
-- Key Rule
---_ Use DECIMAL for money
---_ Floating point ≠ exact base-10
@endmindmap
